1
00:00:23,333 --> 00:00:25,708
♪ I THINK IT'S TIME
WE BLOW THIS SCENE. ♪

2
00:00:25,791 --> 00:00:28,291
♪ GET EVERYBODY
AND THEIR STUFF TOGETHER. ♪

3
00:00:28,375 --> 00:00:31,416
♪ OK, 3, 2, 1.
LET'S JAM. ♪

4
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,375
[BUBBLING]

5
00:02:17,666 --> 00:02:20,083
FROZEN. FROZEN HARD.

6
00:02:20,166 --> 00:02:22,541
YEAH. THEY'RE NO GOOD.

7
00:02:22,625 --> 00:02:23,291
UGH.

8
00:02:23,375 --> 00:02:24,708
FULL OF TOXIC DIOXINS.

9
00:02:24,791 --> 00:02:30,000
I SAVED THESE FOR EVIDENCE
A WHILE BACK, BUT... HUH?

10
00:02:30,083 --> 00:02:31,375
HEY, HOLD ON!

11
00:02:31,458 --> 00:02:32,791
I KNOW YOU'RE HUNGRY,
BUT THOSE THINGS ARE POISON!

12
00:02:32,875 --> 00:02:35,541
[MUNCHING LOUDLY]

13
00:02:35,625 --> 00:02:37,833
A CONFIDENCE MAN
WHO CONS WOMEN

14
00:02:37,916 --> 00:02:39,625
THAT'S WHO YOU WANT TO CATCH?

15
00:02:39,708 --> 00:02:41,083
I DON'T HAVE MUCH CHOICE.

16
00:02:41,166 --> 00:02:42,958
IS HE A BIG, TOUGH CROOK?

17
00:02:43,041 --> 00:02:44,291
SMALLEST OF THE SMALL FRIES.

18
00:02:44,375 --> 00:02:47,208
SPIKE'S GOING TO HATE IT
WHEN I TELL HIM ABOUT IT.

19
00:02:47,291 --> 00:02:48,208
UGH.

20
00:02:48,291 --> 00:02:51,750
EDWARD WANTS CHOCOLATE!

21
00:02:51,833 --> 00:02:55,250
GUESS I'LL DO IT ALONE, THEN.

22
00:02:56,791 --> 00:02:58,625
YOU'VE GOT TO BE KIDDING!

23
00:02:58,708 --> 00:03:03,041
[PANTING]

24
00:03:03,125 --> 00:03:05,750
[BARKING]

25
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:06,833
HMM?

26
00:03:06,916 --> 00:03:08,875
OH, CUT ME SOME SLACK.

27
00:03:08,958 --> 00:03:10,583
[BARKING]

28
00:03:10,666 --> 00:03:12,958
[SNORING]

29
00:03:13,041 --> 00:03:15,250
[SNIFFING]

30
00:03:15,333 --> 00:03:16,583
[MOANS]

31
00:03:16,666 --> 00:03:18,166
IT STINKS!

32
00:03:18,250 --> 00:03:19,583
OOH!

33
00:03:19,666 --> 00:03:21,000
UGH!

34
00:03:21,083 --> 00:03:24,125
REALLY, WEREN'T YOU TAUGHT
TO CLEAN UP YOUR OWN POOP?

35
00:03:24,208 --> 00:03:26,666
LIKE, BURY IT OR SOMETHING?

36
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:33,083
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO FIGURE OUT
WHO IT IS YOU REMIND ME OF.

37
00:03:33,166 --> 00:03:34,166
NOW I KNOW.

38
00:03:34,250 --> 00:03:36,041
IT'S THAT GUY WITH
THE THIN EYEBROWS

39
00:03:36,125 --> 00:03:38,750
WITNEY HAGAS MATSUMOTO.

40
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:40,458
I WONDER WHY I SUDDENLY

41
00:03:40,541 --> 00:03:42,750
THOUGHT OF HIM OUT OF
THE BLUE LIKE THAT.

42
00:03:42,833 --> 00:03:46,208
DO YOU WANT TO KNOW
A SECRET ABOUT MY PAST?

43
00:03:46,291 --> 00:03:47,416
DO YOU?

44
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:49,041
[YAWNS]

45
00:04:08,750 --> 00:04:12,666
MISS MANLY, DOES IT LOOK LIKE
THE PATIENT IS REVIVING?

46
00:04:12,750 --> 00:04:14,500
WHY, YES, DOCTOR.
I BELIEVE SHE IS.

47
00:04:14,583 --> 00:04:18,583
MISS MANLY, DOES SHE LOOK
LIKE AN OLD WOMAN TO YOU?

48
00:04:18,666 --> 00:04:20,291
NO, SHE DOESN'T, DOCTOR.

49
00:04:20,375 --> 00:04:23,708
DO YOU THINK SHE'S BEEN
SUCCESSFULLY UNFROZEN?

50
00:04:23,791 --> 00:04:25,208
I BELIEVE SO, DOCTOR.

51
00:04:25,291 --> 00:04:29,375
CAN YOU HEAR ME?
HUH? YOOHOO.

52
00:04:29,458 --> 00:04:30,541
I AM DR. BACCHUS

53
00:04:30,625 --> 00:04:32,500
BACCHUS, AS IN
THE BACCHUS THAT DROWNED

54
00:04:32,583 --> 00:04:35,333
MORE HUMANS THAN NEPTUNE.

55
00:04:35,416 --> 00:04:37,791
HAVE YOU EVER HEARD
ABOUT THAT BACCHUS?

56
00:04:37,875 --> 00:04:38,958
HMM?

57
00:04:39,041 --> 00:04:40,708
WELL, I USED TO BE
AN ALCOHOLIC BACK THEN.

58
00:04:40,791 --> 00:04:43,583
BACCHUS WAS DROWNING
BECAUSE OF BACCHUS.

59
00:04:43,666 --> 00:04:44,958
HEY, THAT WAS A GOOD ONE.

60
00:04:45,041 --> 00:04:47,583
[LAUGHING MANIACALLY]

61
00:04:50,125 --> 00:04:52,708
OH. NOW, OPEN NICE AND WIDE.

62
00:04:52,791 --> 00:04:54,166
AHH.

63
00:04:54,250 --> 00:04:55,000
MMHMM.

64
00:04:55,083 --> 00:04:56,500
YOU'RE HEALING BEAUTIFULLY.

65
00:04:56,583 --> 00:04:58,583
NO WOUNDS LEFT, AND THE CELLS
ARE DIVIDING QUITE NICELY.

66
00:04:58,666 --> 00:05:00,541
SO YOU ONLY HAVE
ONE PROBLEM LEFT,

67
00:05:00,625 --> 00:05:02,250
AND YOU KNOW WHAT THAT IS, HUH?

68
00:05:02,333 --> 00:05:04,166
COMING UP WITH
30 MILLION WOOLONGS

69
00:05:04,250 --> 00:05:06,083
FOR THE BASIC OPERATION,

70
00:05:06,166 --> 00:05:09,291
IN ADDITION TO 54 YEARS
OF INTEREST PAYMENTS.

71
00:05:09,375 --> 00:05:11,125
UH, HOW MUCH IS THAT?

72
00:05:11,208 --> 00:05:12,000
273 MILLION.

73
00:05:12,083 --> 00:05:13,541
ADD THE HOSPITAL FEES TO THAT,

74
00:05:13,625 --> 00:05:18,125
AND THE TOTAL IS
300,280,000 WOOLONGS.

75
00:05:18,208 --> 00:05:19,458
RIGHT!

76
00:05:19,541 --> 00:05:20,916
SO WHEN YOU'VE PAID
THAT AMOUNT, YOU'LL BE FREE.

77
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,041
YOU UNDERSTAND?

78
00:05:22,125 --> 00:05:23,291
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

79
00:05:23,375 --> 00:05:25,541
GOOD! THEN EVERYTHING'S
JUST-- WHAT DID YOU SAY?

80
00:05:25,625 --> 00:05:28,250
THIS PLACE... WHERE IS IT?

81
00:05:28,333 --> 00:05:29,708
WHERE AM I?

82
00:05:29,791 --> 00:05:30,916
WHO ARE YOU?

83
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:35,000
[LAUGHING]

84
00:05:35,083 --> 00:05:36,291
MISS MANLY?

85
00:05:36,375 --> 00:05:40,166
SHE IS NOT ACTING, DOCTOR.

86
00:05:43,708 --> 00:05:47,583
I AM WITNEY HAGAS MATSUMOTO,
YOUR LAWYER.

87
00:05:47,666 --> 00:05:48,916
LAWYER?

88
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,750
TOTUS INSURANCE COMPANY
BROUGHT ME IN ON THE CASE.

89
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:53,583
I'VE ALREADY
DONE SOME RESEARCH

90
00:05:53,666 --> 00:05:57,500
ON YOUR PAST,
MISS FAYE VALENTINE.

91
00:05:57,583 --> 00:05:59,500
IS THAT REALLY MY NAME?

92
00:05:59,583 --> 00:06:01,708
IT'S AN ESPECIALLY
LOVELY NAME.

93
00:06:01,791 --> 00:06:04,375
I THINK IT SUITS YOU VERY WELL.

94
00:06:04,458 --> 00:06:05,708
AND SO...?

95
00:06:05,791 --> 00:06:08,000
WE NEED TO KNOW
ABOUT YOUR MEMORY.

96
00:06:08,083 --> 00:06:09,000
HMM.

97
00:06:09,083 --> 00:06:11,500
THAT'S A MONITOR,
A HOT WATER POT.

98
00:06:11,583 --> 00:06:12,625
THAT'S A CELLULAR PHONE.

99
00:06:12,708 --> 00:06:14,625
SO I REMEMBER EVERYTHING,

100
00:06:14,708 --> 00:06:18,125
REALLY... EVERYTHING
EXCEPT MY OWN LIFE.

101
00:06:18,208 --> 00:06:19,291
I SEE.

102
00:06:19,375 --> 00:06:20,458
AND?

103
00:06:20,541 --> 00:06:21,750
AND ACCORDING TO
THE RECORDS THAT WE HAVE,

104
00:06:21,833 --> 00:06:22,750
WHEN YOU WERE 20

105
00:06:22,833 --> 00:06:24,791
WELL, IN A SENSE,
YOU STILL ARE 20

106
00:06:24,875 --> 00:06:27,541
YOU WERE INVOLVED IN
A SERIOUS ACCIDENT.

107
00:06:27,625 --> 00:06:28,250
ACCIDENT?

108
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:29,333
THEY COULDN'T SAVE YOU

109
00:06:29,416 --> 00:06:31,541
WITH THE MEDICAL
TECHNOLOGY BACK THEN.

110
00:06:31,625 --> 00:06:33,208
BUT I'M TOTALLY FINE.

111
00:06:33,291 --> 00:06:34,208
YOU CAN SEE THAT.

112
00:06:34,291 --> 00:06:36,250
I DON'T HAVE A SCRATCH.

113
00:06:36,333 --> 00:06:37,166
"BACK THEN"?

114
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:38,166
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

115
00:06:38,250 --> 00:06:40,750
THE ACCIDENT
IT WAS 54 YEARS AGO.

116
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:41,708
[GASPS]

117
00:06:41,791 --> 00:06:43,291
YOU WERE PUT
INTO A COLD SLEEP

118
00:06:43,375 --> 00:06:46,791
IN OTHER WORDS, CRYOGENICALLY
PRESERVED, UNTIL NOW.

119
00:06:46,875 --> 00:06:49,125
MEDICAL TECHNOLOGY HAS
FINALLY ADVANCED TO A POINT

120
00:06:49,208 --> 00:06:52,791
WHERE YOU COULD BE FULLY
CURED AND REAWAKENED.

121
00:06:52,875 --> 00:06:56,708
YOU MIGHT SAY YOU'RE A MODERN
VERSION OF SLEEPING BEAUTY.

122
00:06:56,791 --> 00:06:57,791
YOU'RE KIDDING ME.

123
00:06:57,875 --> 00:06:59,791
I'M VERY SERIOUS, FAYE.

124
00:06:59,875 --> 00:07:02,583
THEN... I'M DREAMING.

125
00:07:02,666 --> 00:07:04,041
[SIGHS]

126
00:07:04,125 --> 00:07:07,333
LISTEN TO ME.
THE YEAR IS 2068.

127
00:07:07,416 --> 00:07:09,208
THIS IS NOT A MONITOR.

128
00:07:09,291 --> 00:07:11,166
IT'S A WASHING MACHINE.

129
00:07:11,250 --> 00:07:12,500
[BEEP BEEP]

130
00:07:12,583 --> 00:07:14,083
THIS ISN'T A HOT WATER POT.

131
00:07:14,166 --> 00:07:15,500
IT'S A FACE CLEANER.

132
00:07:15,583 --> 00:07:17,083
AND THIS IS NOT A CELL PHONE.

133
00:07:17,166 --> 00:07:18,291
IT'S A BIOTHERMOMETER.

134
00:07:18,375 --> 00:07:20,208
YOU PUT THE ROUND END
IN YOUR MOUTH, AND--

135
00:07:20,291 --> 00:07:21,750
LIAR!

136
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:24,125
YOU THINK I'M GOING TO BELIEVE
A LOAD OF RUBBISH LIKE THAT?

137
00:07:24,208 --> 00:07:25,083
UNH!

138
00:07:25,166 --> 00:07:26,416
[BEEP]

139
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:30,000
TEMPERATURE 94.1,
PULSE 54, BLOOD PRESSURE 40/75.

140
00:07:30,083 --> 00:07:31,875
IT'S STILL LOW.
HOLD ON!

141
00:07:31,958 --> 00:07:34,000
YOUR MEMORY IS TRAPPED
IN AN EARLIER ERA,

142
00:07:34,083 --> 00:07:35,958
WHEN CELL PHONES
HAD SOLAR ANTENNAS.

143
00:07:36,041 --> 00:07:38,875
THEN TELL ME
WHAT KIND OF ACCIDENT?!

144
00:07:38,958 --> 00:07:40,000
I NEED TO KNOW!

145
00:07:40,083 --> 00:07:41,833
WHAT WAS I LIKE BEFORE?

146
00:07:41,916 --> 00:07:42,875
CALM DOWN.

147
00:07:42,958 --> 00:07:44,041
IF YOU GET TOO EXCITED,
YOU COULD--

148
00:07:44,125 --> 00:07:46,416
WHAT? WHAT'S GOING
TO HAPPEN TO ME IF I...

149
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:47,708
UH...

150
00:07:47,791 --> 00:07:48,625
[SIGHS]

151
00:07:48,708 --> 00:07:50,916
YOU'LL PASS OUT, FAYE.

152
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:51,791
[SIGHS]

153
00:07:51,875 --> 00:07:53,833
OH, BROTHER.

154
00:07:53,916 --> 00:07:56,083
[TROPICAL BIRD CHIRPING]

155
00:08:07,541 --> 00:08:09,875
[ALARM SOUNDS]

156
00:08:20,250 --> 00:08:22,958
[VEHICLE SPEEDS PAST]

157
00:08:23,041 --> 00:08:25,375
OH? OH.

158
00:08:36,208 --> 00:08:37,750
AAH!

159
00:08:37,833 --> 00:08:39,875
HEY THERE!
WANT A COLD ONE?

160
00:08:39,958 --> 00:08:41,041
AAH!

161
00:08:41,125 --> 00:08:45,750
[LAUGHING]

162
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:49,000
[PANTING]

163
00:08:49,083 --> 00:08:52,125
OH.

164
00:08:52,208 --> 00:08:53,500
OH!

165
00:08:53,583 --> 00:08:57,458
HEY! HEY! HEY!

166
00:09:02,416 --> 00:09:03,375
OH!

167
00:09:03,458 --> 00:09:04,875
WAIT! COME BACK HERE!

168
00:09:04,958 --> 00:09:08,541
[PANTING]

169
00:09:08,625 --> 00:09:11,166
[WHIMPERING]

170
00:09:20,333 --> 00:09:22,916
OH!

171
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,875
MISS VALENTINE!
HELLO!

172
00:09:25,958 --> 00:09:27,625
UNH!

173
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:32,958
OH, OH, AAH!

174
00:09:33,041 --> 00:09:34,250
WAIT! PLEASE!

175
00:09:34,333 --> 00:09:35,875
STAY AWAY FROM ME!

176
00:09:35,958 --> 00:09:37,916
WHAT DO YOU GET
BY RUNNING AWAY?

177
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:40,041
[WHIMPERING]

178
00:09:40,125 --> 00:09:42,958
AAH!

179
00:09:43,041 --> 00:09:44,458
[PANTING]

180
00:09:44,541 --> 00:09:47,041
LISTEN,
MISS VALENTINE, PLEASE.

181
00:09:47,125 --> 00:09:48,916
[CRYING]

182
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,833
I CAN'T PAY 300 MILLION.

183
00:09:50,916 --> 00:09:52,833
IT'S NOT FAIR TO REVIVE ME

184
00:09:52,916 --> 00:09:58,500
AND THEN EXPECT ME TO
PAY ALL THAT MONEY.

185
00:09:58,583 --> 00:10:02,500
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT MYSELF.

186
00:10:02,583 --> 00:10:04,791
WHAT AM I GOING TO DO?

187
00:10:04,875 --> 00:10:08,000
[SOBBING]

188
00:10:08,083 --> 00:10:10,916
YOU CAN DEAL WITH THE DEBT
PAYMENTS LITTLE BY LITTLE.

189
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:13,208
I'LL DO EVERYTHING
I CAN TO HELP YOU.

190
00:10:13,291 --> 00:10:19,166
AND, YOU KNOW, SOMEDAY YOUR
MEMORY MIGHT COME BACK TO YOU.

191
00:10:19,250 --> 00:10:23,375
IF YOU HANG IN THERE, YOU
MIGHT MEET SOMEONE WONDERFUL.

192
00:10:23,458 --> 00:10:25,958
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

193
00:10:34,458 --> 00:10:37,416
WHAT'S THIS?

194
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:38,666
IT'S AN I.D.

195
00:10:38,750 --> 00:10:40,666
IF YOU SHOULD DIE,
OR IF YOU FORGET YOURSELF,

196
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:45,416
THEY KNOW WHO YOU ARE
AND WHERE YOU'RE FROM.

197
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:47,083
I DON'T EVEN HAVE ONE.

198
00:10:47,166 --> 00:10:50,750
I DON'T HAVE AN I.D. AT ALL.

199
00:10:50,833 --> 00:10:52,333
[STOMACH GROWLING]

200
00:10:52,416 --> 00:10:53,958
♪ SOMETIMES I THINK ♪

201
00:10:54,041 --> 00:10:59,125
♪ OH, YES, I'D MOVE TO WHERE ALL
THE SHOOTING STARS ARE GONE ♪

202
00:10:59,208 --> 00:11:04,583
♪ WITH ALL OF OUR WISHES ♪

203
00:11:05,416 --> 00:11:07,333
♪ HOW COULD THEY BEAR ♪

204
00:11:07,416 --> 00:11:12,791
♪ OH, NO, TO CARRY AROUND
THE STUPID HUMAN HOPES? ♪

205
00:11:12,875 --> 00:11:17,458
♪ SO I'M GOING TO HELP ♪

206
00:11:17,541 --> 00:11:18,958
♪ I WILL ♪

207
00:11:19,041 --> 00:11:25,291
♪ GIVE ME A KEY TO LOCK THE DOOR
TO THE SECRET PARADISE ♪

208
00:11:25,375 --> 00:11:29,000
♪ THERE ARE SO MANY QUEUING UP ♪

209
00:11:29,083 --> 00:11:34,333
♪ AND I WON'T LET THEM IN ♪

210
00:11:34,416 --> 00:11:35,625
♪ LOOK AT THEM ♪

211
00:11:35,708 --> 00:11:36,750
♪ THEY ARE CHEEKY ♪

212
00:11:36,833 --> 00:11:42,083
♪ THEY ARE NEVER
WORTHY TO BE SAVED ♪

213
00:11:42,166 --> 00:11:49,458
♪ LAY YOUR HEART, LAY YOUR SOUL
UPON MY MAGIC CARPET... ♪

214
00:11:49,541 --> 00:11:50,625
WHAT'S THAT?

215
00:11:50,708 --> 00:11:51,708
COLLECTION AGENTS.

216
00:11:51,791 --> 00:11:53,333
THE INSURANCE COMPANY
GOT IMPATIENT.

217
00:11:53,416 --> 00:11:55,500
WHAT DO WE DO?

218
00:11:55,583 --> 00:11:58,416
♪ REMEMBER, SURRENDER ♪

219
00:11:58,500 --> 00:12:01,250
♪ THERE'S NOTHING YOU CAN DO ♪

220
00:12:01,333 --> 00:12:04,208
♪ 'CAUSE LOVE'S SUCH A JOKE ♪

221
00:12:04,291 --> 00:12:07,000
♪ LIKE A LITTLE
JACK-IN-THE-BOX... ♪

222
00:12:07,083 --> 00:12:09,291
IF WE STAY HERE,
WE'LL BOTH GET CAUGHT.

223
00:12:09,375 --> 00:12:10,958
YOU'D BETTER
JUMP OUT AND RUN.

224
00:12:11,041 --> 00:12:12,041
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

225
00:12:12,125 --> 00:12:14,166
I'LL MEET YOU
AT THE MEDICAL CLINIC.

226
00:12:14,250 --> 00:12:15,250
ALL RIGHT?

227
00:12:15,333 --> 00:12:16,875
BUT WHY ARE YOU
HELPING ME LIKE THIS?

228
00:12:16,958 --> 00:12:20,250
A PRINCE HAS TO PROTECT
SLEEPING BEAUTY.

229
00:12:20,333 --> 00:12:22,625
THAT'S THE WAY IT WORKS.

230
00:12:26,291 --> 00:12:28,041
[PANTING]

231
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:33,125
[EXPLOSION]

232
00:12:33,208 --> 00:12:37,291
OH!

233
00:12:37,375 --> 00:12:38,500
[SOBS]

234
00:12:38,583 --> 00:12:40,166
WE JUST WENT THROUGH
ALL OF HIS PAPERWORK.

235
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:42,125
IN THE EVENT OF
AN UNFORESEEN ACCIDENT,

236
00:12:42,208 --> 00:12:43,625
HIS INSTRUCTIONS
WERE TO TRANSFER

237
00:12:43,708 --> 00:12:45,208
ALL OF HIS ASSETS TO YOU.

238
00:12:45,291 --> 00:12:47,000
IF YOU GIVE US
A THUMBPRINT HERE,

239
00:12:47,083 --> 00:12:50,250
EVERYTHING HE OWNS
WILL BE YOURS.

240
00:12:50,333 --> 00:12:51,250
OH!

241
00:12:51,333 --> 00:12:53,208
OH, WITNEY!

242
00:12:53,291 --> 00:12:55,625
HE REALLY DID CARE.

243
00:12:55,708 --> 00:12:56,541
[CRYING]

244
00:12:56,625 --> 00:12:59,666
SO... PRESS THIS
WITH YOUR THUMB.

245
00:12:59,750 --> 00:13:01,000
[BEEPING]

246
00:13:01,083 --> 00:13:03,500
[GASPS]

247
00:13:06,041 --> 00:13:08,500
WHY ARE ALL THE NUMBERS
THERE IN RED?

248
00:13:08,583 --> 00:13:09,916
HMM.

249
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:12,208
THOSE ARE ALL HIS DEBTS,
BUT THEY SAY DEBT IS AN ASSET.

250
00:13:12,291 --> 00:13:13,458
HIS DEBTS?

251
00:13:13,541 --> 00:13:16,208
[LAUGHING]

252
00:13:16,291 --> 00:13:20,333
YOU HAVE GOT TO BE KIDDING!

253
00:13:20,416 --> 00:13:22,666
OF COURSE, I CAN SEE
NOW HOW STUPID I WAS.

254
00:13:22,750 --> 00:13:26,833
I MEAN, IF YOU THINK ABOUT IT,
HE RISKED HIS LIFE TO SAVE ME.

255
00:13:26,916 --> 00:13:31,791
AND HIS DEBT WELL, IT WAS A DROP
IN THE BUCKET COMPARED TO MINE.

256
00:13:31,875 --> 00:13:36,291
ALL IN ALL, IT REALLY
WASN'T THAT MUCH.

257
00:13:36,375 --> 00:13:37,500
HUH? OH!

258
00:13:37,583 --> 00:13:40,833
[TOILET FLUSHES]

259
00:13:40,916 --> 00:13:43,541
HOW LONG WERE YOU IN
THERE LISTENING, SPIKE?

260
00:13:43,625 --> 00:13:45,416
TOO LONG.
YOUR STORY NEEDS EDITING.

261
00:13:55,166 --> 00:13:56,458
YOU SHOULD BE ASHAMED,
YOU KNOW.

262
00:13:56,541 --> 00:13:59,708
I'M SURE THAT GUY'S CRYING
IN THE NEXT WORLD...

263
00:13:59,791 --> 00:14:02,291
SINCE HE RAN OFF
WITHOUT PAYING HIS DEBT.

264
00:14:02,375 --> 00:14:03,416
I CAN'T HELP THAT.

265
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:05,500
IT'S WAY MORE THAN
I COULD EVER PAY.

266
00:14:05,583 --> 00:14:07,083
NOW SHE GETS HUFFY ABOUT IT.

267
00:14:07,166 --> 00:14:08,125
WHY SHOULDN'T I?

268
00:14:08,208 --> 00:14:10,375
REMEMBER, I'M A LOT
OLDER THAN YOU.

269
00:14:10,458 --> 00:14:12,458
YOUR PAST IS ALWAYS CHANGING.

270
00:14:12,541 --> 00:14:14,500
LAST TIME, YOU SAID
YOU WERE A GYPSY.

271
00:14:14,583 --> 00:14:16,458
MAYBE YOU MADE
THIS STORY UP, TOO.

272
00:14:16,541 --> 00:14:18,666
THINK WHAT YOU LIKE,
BUT IT'S NOT A LIE.

273
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:21,250
I JUST DON'T KNOW
THE WHOLE TRUTH, ALL RIGHT?

274
00:14:21,333 --> 00:14:23,583
THERE'S NOTHING
I CAN DO ABOUT IT.

275
00:14:23,666 --> 00:14:26,333
WELCOME BACK!

276
00:14:29,458 --> 00:14:32,041
THIS GUY HAS A REP
AS A DON JUAN.

277
00:14:32,125 --> 00:14:34,583
HE'S REALLY JUST
A CHEAP CONFIDENCE MAN.

278
00:14:34,666 --> 00:14:36,041
GIRLS FALL FOR HIM?

279
00:14:36,125 --> 00:14:41,458
TAKE NOTE, WHEN OTHERS ARE
SNOOZING, JET IS ON THE JOB.

280
00:14:41,541 --> 00:14:43,375
MMMH.

281
00:14:43,458 --> 00:14:45,083
MMMH!

282
00:14:45,166 --> 00:14:48,833
OH... UH... UNH!

283
00:14:48,916 --> 00:14:51,041
AAH!

284
00:14:51,125 --> 00:14:55,208
WITNEY HAGAS MATSUMOTO!

285
00:14:55,291 --> 00:14:56,125
UH, YEAH.

286
00:14:56,208 --> 00:14:58,458
LONG TIME NO SEE.

287
00:14:58,541 --> 00:14:59,708
ALL RIGHT, SHE KNOWS HIM,

288
00:14:59,791 --> 00:15:01,750
BUT WHY DOES SHE HAVE
TO TALK TO HIM ALONE?

289
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:03,916
APPARENTLY,
THEY WERE VERY CLOSE.

290
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,375
WE TALKIN' EX-BOYFRIEND?

291
00:15:05,458 --> 00:15:07,041
YEAH, AND THEY WERE
MADE FOR EACH OTHER.

292
00:15:07,125 --> 00:15:10,416
LOOKS LIKE YOU'VE BEEN LIVING
VERY WELL, MR. LAWYER.

293
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:12,583
WHY, BECAUSE I'M
A LITTLE PLUMP?

294
00:15:12,666 --> 00:15:13,708
ISN'T THAT BIASED?

295
00:15:13,791 --> 00:15:15,958
I WANT A FULL EXPLANATION.

296
00:15:16,041 --> 00:15:17,958
WELL, I JUST
HAD A FAT IMPLANT.

297
00:15:18,041 --> 00:15:19,375
IT WAS RIGHT AFTER THE ACCIDENT.

298
00:15:19,458 --> 00:15:21,708
THEY SQUEEZE IT IN THROUGH
THE ARMPIT WITH A PLASTIC

299
00:15:21,791 --> 00:15:23,208
NOT THAT!

300
00:15:23,291 --> 00:15:24,500
[SIGHS]

301
00:15:24,583 --> 00:15:26,458
IT'S BEEN OVER 3 YEARS.

302
00:15:26,541 --> 00:15:28,416
YOU LOOK... HEALTHY.

303
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:29,750
THANKS A LOT.

304
00:15:29,833 --> 00:15:31,375
WERE YOU TRYING TO CREATE
A WHOLE NEW IDENTITY?

305
00:15:31,458 --> 00:15:35,500
I WANTED TO START ALL
OVER... START FROM SCRATCH.

306
00:15:35,583 --> 00:15:37,458
BY CONNING WOMEN
OUT OF THEIR MONEY?

307
00:15:37,541 --> 00:15:39,416
WELL, YOU BECAME
A BOUNTY HUNTER.

308
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:40,750
I'D SAY IT WAS DESTINY.

309
00:15:40,833 --> 00:15:43,125
SO EVERYONE WAS IN ON IT, HUH?

310
00:15:43,208 --> 00:15:44,875
I HAD NO CHOICE.

311
00:15:44,958 --> 00:15:46,458
THE DOCTOR WAS PROTECTING ME.

312
00:15:46,541 --> 00:15:48,500
I OWED TOO MUCH,
AND NOW HE'S DEAD.

313
00:15:48,583 --> 00:15:51,291
MAYBE I SHOULD HAVE JUST LET
THEM COME AND ARREST ME.

314
00:15:51,375 --> 00:15:53,375
I COULDN'T ASK FOR MORE

315
00:15:53,458 --> 00:15:58,000
THAN TO HAVE YOU HAND
ME OVER TO THE POLICE.

316
00:15:58,083 --> 00:16:00,541
YOU THINK IT'S SAFE
TO LEAVE THEM ALONE?

317
00:16:00,625 --> 00:16:02,083
WORRIED ABOUT HIM OR HER?

318
00:16:02,166 --> 00:16:04,333
I'M AFRAID SHE MIGHT
LET HIM ESCAPE OR SOMETHING.

319
00:16:04,416 --> 00:16:06,333
WELL, SHE'D HAVE TO
HAVE A HEART TO DO THAT.

320
00:16:06,416 --> 00:16:08,583
DON'T BE FOOLED
BECAUSE SHE ACTS TOUGH.

321
00:16:08,666 --> 00:16:10,625
BABES LIKE HER ARE
THE FIRST ONES TO GO SOFT

322
00:16:10,708 --> 00:16:12,916
WHEN IT COMES TO
AN OLD BOYFRIEND.

323
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:14,083
IS THAT RIGHT?

324
00:16:14,166 --> 00:16:15,250
WOMEN ARE HOPELESS.

325
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:17,416
THEY DON'T WORK ON REASON.

326
00:16:17,500 --> 00:16:21,125
WE'RE HERE!
WELCOME, VISITORS!

327
00:16:21,208 --> 00:16:23,416
SO, ARE YOU THE ONES
THAT CONTACTED US?

328
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:26,208
YEAH.
WANT TO CLAIM A BOUNTY.

329
00:16:26,291 --> 00:16:27,416
HMM. I SEE.

330
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:30,041
MISS MANLY,
PREPARE FOR RENDEZVOUS.

331
00:16:30,125 --> 00:16:31,708
YES, DOCTOR.

332
00:16:31,791 --> 00:16:39,500
I'M GLAD I GOT TO SEE YOU ONE
LAST TIME... SLEEPING BEAUTY.

333
00:16:43,833 --> 00:16:45,166
LET'S GO.

334
00:16:45,250 --> 00:16:46,166
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

335
00:16:46,250 --> 00:16:47,583
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO DO THIS FOR ME.

336
00:16:47,666 --> 00:16:49,375
IT'S TOO RISKY.

337
00:16:49,458 --> 00:16:50,833
[GUNSHOT]

338
00:16:53,541 --> 00:16:54,375
--HMM?
--HUH?

339
00:16:54,458 --> 00:16:56,083
THEY OPENED THE HATCH ALREADY?

340
00:16:56,166 --> 00:16:57,500
HE'S TRYING TO GET OUT.

341
00:16:57,583 --> 00:16:58,791
SHE'S HELPING HIM.

342
00:16:58,875 --> 00:16:59,625
WANT TO BET?

343
00:16:59,708 --> 00:17:01,958
YEAH. I'LL GIVE YOU 4 TO 1.

344
00:17:02,041 --> 00:17:03,375
[BOTH GRUNTING]

345
00:17:03,458 --> 00:17:05,000
DAMN IT, HURRY UP, SPIKE!

346
00:17:05,083 --> 00:17:06,375
I'M TRYING!

347
00:17:06,458 --> 00:17:07,208
WHOA!

348
00:17:07,291 --> 00:17:08,166
IT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

349
00:17:08,250 --> 00:17:09,291
WE'LL NEVER MAKE IT.

350
00:17:09,375 --> 00:17:10,750
YOU CAN'T SQUEEZE
TWO PEOPLE IN HERE.

351
00:17:10,833 --> 00:17:12,208
JUST DON'T BREATHE SO MUCH.

352
00:17:12,291 --> 00:17:13,875
EXHALE OR SOMETHING.

353
00:17:13,958 --> 00:17:15,125
HEY, WAIT!

354
00:17:15,208 --> 00:17:17,458
STAY BACK!
WE'RE LEAVING!

355
00:17:17,541 --> 00:17:18,625
UNH!

356
00:17:18,708 --> 00:17:20,458
SHE WANTS THE GUY
INSTEAD OF THE MONEY.

357
00:17:20,541 --> 00:17:22,166
JET CAUGHT HIM!
IT'S HIS REWARD, FAYE!

358
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:23,500
I HAVE SOME HISTORY
TO WORK OUT WITH THIS GUY,

359
00:17:23,583 --> 00:17:26,125
SO I CLAIM FIRST RIGHTS TO HIM

360
00:17:26,208 --> 00:17:27,708
AND TO THE BOUNTY
THAT'S ON HIS HEAD!

361
00:17:27,791 --> 00:17:30,458
IS IT JUST ME,
OR DID THAT NOT MAKE ANY SENSE?

362
00:17:30,541 --> 00:17:33,541
JUST LIKE I SAID
WOMEN DON'T WORK ON REASON.

363
00:17:33,625 --> 00:17:35,000
GET ME OUT OF HERE!

364
00:17:35,083 --> 00:17:36,625
ARE YOU GOING TO
SET HIM FREE OR WHAT?

365
00:17:36,708 --> 00:17:37,666
WE'LL SEE!

366
00:17:37,750 --> 00:17:38,916
[GUNSHOT]

367
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,458
[BEEPING]

368
00:17:40,541 --> 00:17:42,041
OH, MAN!

369
00:17:42,125 --> 00:17:44,166
UNH!

370
00:17:49,750 --> 00:17:54,750
VISITORS, THANK YOU
FOR YOUR ATTENDANCE!

371
00:17:58,333 --> 00:18:00,083
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

372
00:18:00,166 --> 00:18:03,458
WHAT ARE YOU GOING
TO DO WITH ME?

373
00:18:03,541 --> 00:18:05,416
I WANT TO KNOW THE TRUTH.

374
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:06,125
HUH?

375
00:18:06,208 --> 00:18:07,541
TELL ME, WHO AM I?

376
00:18:07,625 --> 00:18:12,541
TELL ME WHERE THE LIES END
AND THE TRUTH BEGINS.

377
00:18:12,625 --> 00:18:15,333
[CRASH]

378
00:18:15,416 --> 00:18:17,625
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

379
00:18:17,708 --> 00:18:21,708
IF YOU'RE NOT CAREFUL,
I'LL HIT THE COCKPIT.

380
00:18:22,750 --> 00:18:25,708
I'M NOT GOING EASY ON YOU.

381
00:18:27,333 --> 00:18:29,750
I THOUGHT THAT WAS MY LINE.

382
00:18:35,291 --> 00:18:37,208
UNH!

383
00:18:54,166 --> 00:18:56,208
[GASPS]

384
00:19:03,041 --> 00:19:05,958
AAH!

385
00:19:06,041 --> 00:19:10,000
YOU KNOW, YOU REALLY
ARE A BIG PAIN.

386
00:19:16,833 --> 00:19:19,333
WHO AM I?

387
00:19:21,583 --> 00:19:23,125
ARE YOU SURE YOU
REALLY WANT TO KNOW?

388
00:19:23,208 --> 00:19:25,958
IT'S GOING TO BE
HARD TO SWALLOW.

389
00:19:27,416 --> 00:19:31,750
ARE YOU PREPARED FOR
ALL THE CONSEQUENCES?

390
00:19:31,833 --> 00:19:32,708
I AM.

391
00:19:32,791 --> 00:19:36,833
ARE YOU SURE?

392
00:19:36,916 --> 00:19:37,875
SPIT IT OUT!

393
00:19:37,958 --> 00:19:39,833
I DON'T REALLY KNOW
MYSELF. I SWEAR!

394
00:19:39,916 --> 00:19:40,833
YOU'RE LYING.

395
00:19:40,916 --> 00:19:43,208
WHO AM I
MY PAST, MY FUTURE?

396
00:19:43,291 --> 00:19:47,750
THESE ARE QUESTIONS EVERY HUMAN
ASKS AT LEAST ONE IN THEIR LIFE.

397
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:48,666
WHO ARE YOU?

398
00:19:48,750 --> 00:19:49,666
HOWEVER, PUBERTY
IS THE ONLY TIME

399
00:19:49,750 --> 00:19:51,000
TO WORRY ABOUT
THINGS LIKE THAT.

400
00:19:51,083 --> 00:19:52,625
ONLY PEOPLE WHO ARE BORED

401
00:19:52,708 --> 00:19:54,958
THINK SUCH THOUGHTS
AFTER A CERTAIN AGE.

402
00:19:55,041 --> 00:19:58,791
I'VE HEARD THAT VOICE
BEFORE SOMEWHERE.

403
00:19:58,875 --> 00:20:01,166
HERE I AM. YOOHOO!

404
00:20:01,250 --> 00:20:02,333
OH, GEES.

405
00:20:02,416 --> 00:20:04,375
IS THAT THE DOCTOR
FROM THE CRYO CLINIC?

406
00:20:04,458 --> 00:20:05,583
SURE SEEMS THAT WAY.

407
00:20:05,666 --> 00:20:07,208
YOU TOLD ME THAT
DOCTOR WAS DEAD!

408
00:20:07,291 --> 00:20:08,791
UH, UH, NOT DEAD
I MEAN, NOT COMPLETELY.

409
00:20:08,875 --> 00:20:12,791
HOW MANY LIES ARE YOU GOING TO
TELL ME BEFORE YOU'RE THROUGH?

410
00:20:12,875 --> 00:20:14,041
UH, UH, UH...

411
00:20:14,125 --> 00:20:16,916
YOU WERE CRYOGENICALLY
PRESERVED IN OUR LABS.

412
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:17,750
HUH?

413
00:20:17,833 --> 00:20:19,333
THAT IS A VERIFIABLE FACT.

414
00:20:19,416 --> 00:20:20,708
I CAN GUARANTEE IT.

415
00:20:20,791 --> 00:20:21,708
HUH?

416
00:20:21,791 --> 00:20:22,875
WHAT ABOUT MY PAST?

417
00:20:22,958 --> 00:20:24,083
WHO IN THE WORLD AM I?

418
00:20:24,166 --> 00:20:26,541
ACTUALLY, I GAVE YOU
THE NAME "VALENTINE."

419
00:20:26,625 --> 00:20:28,833
YES, I NAMED YOU AFTER
MY FAVORITE LOVE SONG.

420
00:20:28,916 --> 00:20:30,291
ALL THE OTHER
DATA ON YOU WAS LOST

421
00:20:30,375 --> 00:20:31,750
WHEN THE ASTRAL GATE EXPLODED.

422
00:20:31,833 --> 00:20:33,500
SO, YOU SEE,
NO ONE KNOWS WHO YOU ARE

423
00:20:33,583 --> 00:20:38,041
OR WHY YOU WERE PUT
IN A CRYOGENIC STATE.

424
00:20:38,125 --> 00:20:40,750
IS THIS GUY A DOCTOR OR A COP?

425
00:20:40,833 --> 00:20:41,708
HUH?

426
00:20:41,791 --> 00:20:43,125
PILOTED PATROL SHIP 118.

427
00:20:43,208 --> 00:20:45,458
YOU ARE IN A VEHICLE WHICH
HAS BEEN REPORTED STOLEN.

428
00:20:45,541 --> 00:20:47,750
STATE YOUR DEPARTMENT CODE NOW.

429
00:20:47,833 --> 00:20:49,708
I REPEAT, STATE YOUR CODE.

430
00:20:49,791 --> 00:20:51,416
DOCTOR, THIS IS NOT GOOD.

431
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:52,375
WE'RE GOING TO BE
APPREHENDED HERE.

432
00:20:52,458 --> 00:20:54,333
IT'S VERY UNFORTUNATE,

433
00:20:54,416 --> 00:20:57,291
BUT WE'D BETTER CUT OUR
LOSSES AND MAKE TRACKS.

434
00:20:57,375 --> 00:20:58,125
GOOD CALL, DOCTOR.

435
00:20:58,208 --> 00:20:59,666
YOU'RE ON YOUR OWN, WITNEY.

436
00:20:59,750 --> 00:21:00,750
TAKE CARE OF YOURSELF.

437
00:21:00,833 --> 00:21:02,208
BYE BYE, WITNEY.

438
00:21:02,291 --> 00:21:03,916
UH, WAIT.

439
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:05,583
WAIT A MINUTE, UNCLE!

440
00:21:05,666 --> 00:21:06,625
DON'T GO!

441
00:21:06,708 --> 00:21:08,000
HE'S YOUR UNCLE?

442
00:21:08,083 --> 00:21:09,250
UHHUH.

443
00:21:09,333 --> 00:21:10,791
[GASPS]

444
00:21:13,833 --> 00:21:15,750
HUH?

445
00:21:19,166 --> 00:21:21,583
HMM.

446
00:21:21,666 --> 00:21:22,750
ARRGH!

447
00:21:22,833 --> 00:21:25,166
I'LL TAKE MY BOUNTY
RIGHT HERE AND NOW.

448
00:21:25,250 --> 00:21:30,041
AH, THAT'S BETTER.

449
00:21:30,125 --> 00:21:31,541
AND GOOD RIDDANCE.

450
00:21:31,625 --> 00:21:35,791
WHAT A FITTING PAYBACK FOR
ALL THE SLEAZY LIES YOU TOLD ME.

451
00:21:35,875 --> 00:21:39,333
WELL, THERE IS ONE
PART THAT'S TRUE...

452
00:21:39,416 --> 00:21:43,208
THAT I FELL IN LOVE WITH
YOU WHILE YOU WERE SLEEPING.

453
00:21:43,291 --> 00:21:48,666
I FELL IN LOVE
WITH SLEEPING BEAUTY.

454
00:21:48,750 --> 00:21:49,833
UH, NO! I'M LYING!

455
00:21:49,916 --> 00:21:52,083
IT'S JUST ANOTHER LIE!
YOU KNOW.

456
00:21:52,166 --> 00:21:54,791
HMM.

457
00:21:57,541 --> 00:22:01,125
LOOK WHO'S HERE.
YOU MUST REALLY WANT ME BACK.

458
00:22:01,208 --> 00:22:02,250
YEAH. NICE TRY.

459
00:22:02,333 --> 00:22:04,416
YOU WERE JEALOUS.

460
00:22:04,500 --> 00:22:07,000
IN YOUR DREAMS.

461
00:22:08,625 --> 00:22:09,666
I'M STILL IN THE DARK.

462
00:22:09,750 --> 00:22:12,000
I MAY NEVER KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT MY PAST.

463
00:22:12,083 --> 00:22:13,875
DOESN'T REALLY
MATTER, DOES IT?

464
00:22:13,958 --> 00:22:15,000
EASY FOR YOU TO SAY.

465
00:22:15,083 --> 00:22:16,916
AT LEAST YOU HAVE A PAST.

466
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:18,708
AND YOU HAVE A FUTURE.

467
00:22:18,791 --> 00:22:20,083
THAT'S WHAT COUNTS.

468
00:22:20,166 --> 00:22:21,500
WHAT'S THIS?

469
00:22:21,583 --> 00:22:26,625
IT'S YOUR SHARE OF THE BOUNTY
THE BIG 19,800 REWARD.

470
00:22:26,708 --> 00:22:27,541
YOU'RE KIDDING.

471
00:22:27,625 --> 00:22:31,125
THE SMALLEST OF
THE SMALL FRIES.

472
00:22:31,208 --> 00:22:34,875
SO IT WASN'T 19,800.

473
00:22:34,958 --> 00:22:38,541
I KIND OF PUT
AN EXTRA ZERO IN THERE.

474
00:22:38,625 --> 00:22:40,250
HA HA.

475
00:24:25,708 --> 00:24:29,958
SO I HAVE TO ADMIT, THE NEXT
EPISODE OF "COWBOY BEBOP" IS,

476
00:24:30,041 --> 00:24:32,625
WELL... IT'S KIND OF DEPRESSING.

477
00:24:32,708 --> 00:24:34,208
VERY DEPRESSING, ACTUALLY.

478
00:24:34,291 --> 00:24:36,708
THE ONLY CHARACTERS WHO SHOW UP
ARE A BUNCH OF MUSTY OLD GUYS.

479
00:24:36,791 --> 00:24:40,541
I HATE TO SAY THIS,
BUT IT'S KIND OF HEAVY-HANDED.

480
00:24:40,625 --> 00:24:41,958
CHILDREN SHOULDN'T WATCH IT.

481
00:24:42,041 --> 00:24:42,750
LADIES SHOULD AVOID IT, TOO.

482
00:24:42,833 --> 00:24:44,541
AND ON TOP OF THAT,

483
00:24:44,625 --> 00:24:46,541
IT'S BETTER IF YOU YOUNG
GUYS DON'T TUNE IN, EITHER.

484
00:24:46,625 --> 00:24:48,875
NEXT EPISODE
BLACK DOG SERENADE.

485
00:24:48,958 --> 00:24:51,541
OH, ALL YOU OLD GUYS, I WOULDN'T
MISS THIS ONE IF I WERE YOU.

